hierarchy_analysis.hierarchy_description: Bins exist at the organization level. Each ticket has one bin_id and bin_name. No board information is available in the ticket data, suggesting bins are globally scoped rather than board-scoped.

identifier_strategy: Use bin_id for filtering (globally unique identifier)
recommendations: Bin IDs are sufficient for unique identification
Bin names may not be unique across the organization
Filter by bin_id for exact matching, bin_name for user-friendly filtering
No board data available, so board filtering not possible via this endpoint
Client-side filtering required for both board and bin filtering
